The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Monday, April 18, 2005 

 Vishnukant Shastri dead

 OUR BUREAU

 Patna/Calcutta, April 17: Former Uttar Pradesh governor and Bengal BJP chief Vishnukant Shastri died of a heart attack in the toilet of a train from Howrah just before reaching here. He was 76.

 A communique issued by the BJP?s Bihar unit said Shastri went to the toilet near Bakhtiyarpur. 

 ?When he did not come out even after the train reached Patna, the door to the toilet was broken. A doctor was called to the place but he was declared dead,? it said. 

 Shastri was a first-class first in MA, Hindi, from Calcutta University, where he later taught the language. He was first elected MLA on a Janata Party ticket from Jorabagan in north Calcutta in 1977. 

 The Bengal BJP president for two consecutive terms, Shastri also served the party as its national vice-president. He later became member of the Rajya Sabha and then the governor of Himachal Pradesh before serving in Uttar Pradesh in the same capacity.

 BJP president L.K. Advani and Jharkhand chief minister Arjun Munda are expected to be present during his funeral at Nimtola Ghat crematorium tomorrow. Bihar governor Buta Singh and the Bengal unit of the CPM condoled his death.




